Couple other ones too that people don't think of as much, one<br>
helps you raise factions in another area you may want to do<br>
so in.<br>
<br>
That human guy near the muffin guy is one of them. Bring<br>
him small lanterns and give 4 at a time (or 1? forget) I forget<br>
if its small lanterns too. It raises the same factions as muffins<br>
i think. The thing is, I'd bet this raises them MORE though not<br>
sure (muffins are easier, cheaper, and stack) <br>
<br>
Added benefit to this one is he gives you a wood chip<br>
you can then port to toxula with (these stack too!) and<br>
give them to emil parsini in tox forest (near erudin city) to <br>
raise merchants of erudin which is otherwise pretty hard to<br>
raise if you screw it up (or nearly impossible) I got to glower<br>
on it and got it back up to amiable by doing this.<br>
<br>
Another one many people forget is killing that captain sureshot<br>
with the bracer of erolsi in oot and giving the bracer and  a pirate earring to styria fearnon on sisters island, both of which also raise that faction. As with the lantern one I'd almost bet they raise it more than muffins also.. though it <br>
may seem like its more laborious What I did was bind near her, run over kill surestout and someone else until I had bracer and earring, gate back, give to her, run back over, sit, surestout pops again soon, repeat. As you may imagine this is also nice to do if no one happens to be camping the ac spawn.. you can kill the phs on the way by for jollies. I also got the oracle guy a couple times when I saw him pop on track while doing this.<br>
<br>
Although I've never had to worry about it since I've never lowered factions in POG (I stay the heck out ;)  except to get<br>
quests)  my factions are now super duper warmly with all of those groups. <p><BR>
